    • KeyInformation

      public KeyInformation(byte[] circuitId, InetAddress ipAddress, Key privateKey, PublicKey publicKey, BigInteger u)
      Using this object, a Node can store all the information it needs about it neighbors Ex: An intermediary node will have two such objects, one for the previous node, and one for the next node
      Parameters:
      circuitId - is the id of the circuit the two nodes are part of
      ipAddress - is the ip address of the node that holds this information
